					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">koitsu, but if you don't want to play HD remake, you can just ignore it, correct? There are people with different opinions, who may enjoy it. It may even be not too bad, actually - check <a href="http://blog.circlestorm.org/uploads/Games/MI2-remake-comparison-4.png" class="postlink">Monkey Island 2 HD remake</a> (it allows to switch between the original and remake with a key at any point, by the way).
<br />
<br />The idea to make an emulator that replaces graphics with hi-res and sound with MP3's is old and was proposed many times. I recall it from ~2004, I think. But still no one is really got up to the task, and I think that lack of artists would be a real showstopper. Also, to 'sell' the idea to people you certainly shouldn't use examples like in the first post, it only spoils the idea as it looks inferior to the original.</div>

